{"article_id":"S16P2OTOkGWMiiWS","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Benedict called his choice","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"' a decision of great importance for the life of the church . ' |","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"REUTERS","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"Pope resigning on Feb. 28","depth":2},{"id":4,"text":"VATICAN CITY","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"( AP ) -","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"Pope Benedict XVI announced Monday","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that he would resign on Feb. 28","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"because he was simply too infirm","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"to carry on","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"- the first pontiff","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"to do so in nearly 600 years .","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"The decision sets the stage","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"for a conclave","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"to elect a new pope before the end of March .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"The 85-year-old pope announced his decision in Latin during a meeting of Vatican cardinals on Monday morning .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"He emphasized","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that carrying out the duties","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"of being pope","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"- the leader of more than a billion Roman Catholics worldwide -","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"requires `` both strength of mind and body . ''","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"`` After having repeatedly examined my conscience before God ,","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"I have come to the certainty","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"that my strengths due to an advanced age are no longer suited to an adequate exercise of the Petrine ministry , ''","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"he told the cardinals .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"`` I am well aware","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"that this ministry , due to its essential spiritual nature , must be carried out not only by words and deeds but no less with prayer and suffering . `","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"` However , in today 's world ,","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"subject to so many rapid changes","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"and shaken by questions of deep relevance for the life of faith ,","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"in order to govern the barque of St. Peter","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"and proclaim the Gospel ,","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"both strength of mind and body are necessary","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"- strengths","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"which in the last few months , has deteriorated in me to the extent","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"that I have had to recognize my incapacity","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"to adequately fulfill the ministry","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"entrusted to me . ''","depth":15},{"id":38,"text":"The last pope","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"to resign","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"was Pope Gregory XII ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"who stepped down in 1415 in a deal","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"to end the Great Western Schism among competing papal claimants .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"Benedict called his choice `` a decision of great importance for the life of the church . ''","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"The move sets the stage","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"for the Vatican to hold a conclave","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"to elect a new pope by mid-March ,","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"since the traditional mourning time","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"that would follow the death of a pope","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"does n't have to be observed .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"There are several papal contenders in the wings , but no obvious front-runner","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"- the same situation","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"when Benedict was elected pontiff in 2005 after the death of Pope John Paul II .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"When Benedict was elected pope at age 78","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"- already the oldest pope","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"elected in nearly 300 years -","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"he had been already planning to retire as the Vatican 's chief orthodoxy watchdog","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"to spend his final years","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"writing in the `` peace and quiet '' of his native Bavaria .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Contenders","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"to be his successor","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"include Cardinal Angelo Scola , archbishop of Milan , Cardinal Christoph Schoenborn , the archbishop of Vienna , and Cardinal Marc Ouellet , the Canadian head of the Vatican 's office for bishops .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"Longshots include Cardinal Timothy Dolan of New York .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"Although Dolan is popular","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"and backs the pope 's conservative line ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"the general thinking is that the Catholic Church does n't need a pope from a `` superpower . ''","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"All cardinals under age 80 are allowed to vote in the conclave , the secret meeting","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"held in the Sistine Chapel","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"where cardinals cast ballots","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"to elect a new pope .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"As per tradition , the ballots are burned after each voting round ;","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"black smoke","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"that snakes out of the chimney","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"means no pope has been chosen ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"while white smoke means a pope has been elected .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"Popes are allowed to resign ;","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"church law specifies only","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that the resignation be `` freely made and properly manifested . ''","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"Only a handful have done so , however","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"and there 's good reason","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"why it has n't become commonplace :","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Might the existence of two popes","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"- even when one has stepped down -","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"lead to divisions and instability in the church ?","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"Might a new resignation precedent lead to pressures on future popes to quit at the slightest hint of infirmity ?","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Benedict himself raised the possibility","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"of resigning","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"if he were simply too old or sick","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"to continue on in 2010 ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"when he was interviewed for the book `` Light of the World . ''","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"`` If a pope clearly realizes","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"that he is no longer physically , psychologically and spiritually capable","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"of handling the duties of his office ,","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"then he has a right , and under some circumstances , also an obligation","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"to resign , ''","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Benedict said .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"The former Cardinal Joseph Ratzinger had an intimate view","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"as Pope John Paul II ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"with whom he had worked closely for nearly a quarter-century ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"suffered through the debilitating end of his papacy .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":199,"left":103,"right":198,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":103,"left":102,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":198,"left":104,"right":197,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":104,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":147,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":141,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":113,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":